messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
I have a gun range officer that got shot in the head.
I'm sorry, what's your address?
We're at the last stop on Highway 93.
Okay, I'm getting medical on the line. Hold on.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Mojave County with a transfer. We're at the last stop on Highway 93. A male subject's been shot in the head. Hello?
Hello, is this the last stop?
Yes, it is. Is he breathing?
Yes, he is. He's having convulsions.
Okay, do you need to send EMS right away?
Yes, sir.
Alright, are you applying pressure to the wound?
I can't. I have nothing to apply pressure with.
Do you have any kind of clothing or towels?
Yes, I do.
Okay, if you can get clothing or towels and bunch them up to apply pressure.
We have EMS on the way, okay?
Okay, I'll do that.
Alright, thank you.
Sir? The last stop, 17 miles northwest.
Alright, we need an ambulance to the last stop on North U.S. Highway 93 immediately. We have someone shot.
Yes, please send an ambulance ASAP.
Do you have a call open?
I'm sorry, I'm talking to the other dispatcher. We need an ambulance immediately.
Yes, we're getting medical out there. Stay on the line.
Take him to the restaurant. At the gun range.
We're getting medical on the way. I'm not going to hang up with you.
Alright, we have a report of an accidental shooting at the gun range. We have medical on the way.
Yes, I'm still here. He's still breathing.
Can you tell me where he was shot?
In the head, on the side of the head.
What's his name?
Roger.
How old is he?
He's in his late 30s.
I need a sheriff sent out to a shooting range for an accidental shooting. Do you have them coming?
Yes, sir. Medical and DPS and sheriffs are all on their way.
Alright, thank you.
You're welcome.
Hey, this is Rick at the last stop. We need a helicopter. An ambulance isn't going to work.
Okay, Rick. We've got one on the way.
Where is the helicopter? We need it now.
Let me get medical back on the line for you. Hold on, please.
Mojave County, reference the last stop, sir. They need the helicopter now.
Okay. Is he still breathing?
Yes, he is. Are you applying pressure to the wound?
Yes, I am, but he's convulsing and choking on his own spit.
Are you able to lean him on his side so the spit drains out of his mouth?
Yes, I am. When he bleeds through the cloth, do I put another on top?
Yes, apply more on top but do not peel it away.
Okay, you're okay, Charlie. You're okay.
Please hurry up. We've got medical on the way. We're bending his knee.
Is he able to speak?
No, he's completely unconscious.
Just keep an eye on his breathing, okay?
Alright.
What's the ETA on the helicopter?
I'm not sure. We have people coming by ground as well.
Alright. Tell them to hurry up.
They're on their way, sir.
Are you inside the facility?
No, we're outside on the range.
Alright. When he bleeds through the cloth, apply more on top. Do not peel it away.
Okay. You're alright, Charlie, hang in there.
